---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQs - National Park Directory">
	<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
		<h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-center my-16">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
		
		<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
			<p class="text-lg text-center mb-12">Find answers to common questions about our site and national parks.</p>
			
			<div class="space-y-8">
				<div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">General Questions</h2>
					
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">What is the National Park Directory?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">The National Park Directory is a comprehensive resource for information about national parks across the United States. We provide details about park features, activities, wildlife, and visitor information to help you plan your visits.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Is the information on this site official?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">While we strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, the National Park Directory is not affiliated with the National Park Service. For official information, please visit the NPS website or contact the specific park directly.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">How often is the content updated?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">We update our content regularly to ensure accuracy. Park information is reviewed at least quarterly, and we make immediate updates for significant changes such as park closures or new regulations.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div class="border-b border-gray-200 pb-8">
					<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Planning Your Visit</h2>
					
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Do I need reservations to visit national parks?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">Some popular national parks require reservations, especially during peak seasons. We recommend checking the specific park's requirements well in advance of your planned visit. Many parks also charge entrance fees.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">What is the best time of year to visit national parks?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">The ideal time to visit varies by park. Summer is popular for many parks, but spring and fall often offer pleasant weather with fewer crowds. Winter visits provide unique experiences in parks that remain open year-round.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Are pets allowed in national parks?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">Pet policies vary by park. Most parks allow leashed pets in developed areas but restrict them from trails, backcountry, and visitor buildings. Service animals are generally permitted throughout parks. Check each park's specific pet policies before visiting.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<div>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-4">Using Our Website</h2>
					
					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Can I contribute content to the National Park Directory?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">We welcome contributions from visitors and park enthusiasts. Please contact us through our Contact page if you'd like to share photos, trip reports, or suggestions for our site.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">How can I report inaccurate information?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">If you notice any inaccuracies on our site, please let us know through our Contact page. We appreciate your help in maintaining accurate information for all users.</p>
						</div>
						
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Do you offer a mobile app?</h3>
							<p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">We're currently developing a mobile app that will include offline access to park information, trail maps, and more. Sign up for our newsletter to be notified when it launches.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="mt-12 text-center">
				<p class="text-gray-600">Didn't find what you're looking for?</p>
				<a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center mt-2 text-green-800 font-medium hover:underline">
					Contact Us â†’
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout> 